{"id":3762,"date":"2019-12-04T23:38:43","date_gmt":"2019-12-04T23:38:43","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/?p=3762"},"modified":"2020-11-22T23:39:07","modified_gmt":"2020-11-22T23:39:07","slug":"building-the-future-of-cross-fi","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/building-the-future-of-cross-fi\/","title":{"rendered":"Building The Future of Cross-Fi"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Advantages of Decentralized Finance<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>State of DeFi &amp; Current Primitives<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>Advantages of Decentralized Finance:<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><strong>Permissionless:<\/strong>&nbsp;Anyone is able to access decentralized financial networks through an internet connection. No individual can be denied service based on who they are, where they were born, or how much money they have<\/li><li><strong>Programmable:<\/strong>&nbsp;Developers can create and intertwine financial services at a very low cost. Plug and play architecture helps compound the power of these services<\/li><li><strong>Transparent:<\/strong>&nbsp;Public blockchains are transparent and auditable. They retain best of both worlds: informationon financial exchanges are available while privacy can be preserved<\/li><li><strong>Trustless:&nbsp;<\/strong>Users don\u2019t have to trust a central party to ensure that transactions are valid<\/li><li><strong>Censorship Resistant:<\/strong>&nbsp;No central party is able to reverse the order of transactions and deem a validated transaction invalid at some later point in time. Similarly, a central party can\u2019t turn off the service and anyone with access can use the network<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>Popular DeFi use cases:<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Lending &#8211; Borrowing\/Lending on a public blockchain with much less friction vs. traditional platforms.<\/li><li>Derivatives\/Assets &#8211; Synthetic assets which are derivatives of other assets allows exposure without having the actual asset.<\/li><li>Decentralized Exchanges &#8211; Traders can trade on platforms that do not hold their funds custody<\/li><li>Payment solutions &#8211; Traditionally centralized payment solutions can be decentralized to be as effective while staying censorship-free<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1072\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de997e058e6cb615e54cf48_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.48.13-AM-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3765\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de997e058e6cb615e54cf48_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.48.13-AM-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de997e058e6cb615e54cf48_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.48.13-AM-768x322.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de997e058e6cb615e54cf48_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.48.13-AM-1536x643.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de997e058e6cb615e54cf48_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.48.13-AM-2048x858.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Risk is not removed, but shifted from counterparties to smart contracts<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"978\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de998ae5190954f5f24af52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.54.07-AM-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3767\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de998ae5190954f5f24af52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.54.07-AM-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de998ae5190954f5f24af52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.54.07-AM-768x294.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de998ae5190954f5f24af52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.54.07-AM-1536x587.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de998ae5190954f5f24af52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.54.07-AM-2048x783.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><figcaption>Note: non-exhaustive list, Wave does not make any claims on counterparty or technical risk. Platforms have differing collateralization requirements<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack: Stablecoins<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Stablecoin implementations:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Traditional Collateral-backed<\/li><li>Crypto Collateral-backed<\/li><li>Hybrid \/ Algorithmic<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Traditional Collateral stablecoins include Tether (88% of the total stablecoin market share) and USDC (4.4%)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>MakerDAO\u2019s Dai is the most prominent crypto collateralized stablecoin, with a market cap of ~$86M<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1930\" height=\"912\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9996849103c92b99651cc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.57.14-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3768\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9996849103c92b99651cc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.57.14-AM.jpg 1930w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9996849103c92b99651cc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.57.14-AM-768x363.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9996849103c92b99651cc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-7.57.14-AM-1536x726.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1930px) 100vw, 1930px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack: Lending Protocols<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1060\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9afda49103c0b61970daf_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.32.42-AM-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3770\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9afda49103c0b61970daf_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.32.42-AM-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9afda49103c0b61970daf_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.32.42-AM-768x318.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9afda49103c0b61970daf_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.32.42-AM-1536x636.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9afda49103c0b61970daf_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.32.42-AM-2048x848.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack: Oracles<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Oracles provide smart contracts with data from the outside world (i.e. the price of ETH to trigger a liquidation if collateralization drops below requirements)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Current approaches to ensure validity of oracles include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Multiple data sources &#8211; Safer, but more expensive<\/li><li>Multiple oracles &#8211; Reduces probability of collusion<\/li><li>Financial incentives \/ penalties &#8211; Earn rewards for performing honest work, but penalize if they misbehave<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>There is no one-size-fits-all solution as dApps require different guarantees based on their specific use cases, with the trade-off being safety vs. cost.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1706\" height=\"1390\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b08f519095f3c125a49a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.36.03-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3771\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b08f519095f3c125a49a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.36.03-AM.jpg 1706w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b08f519095f3c125a49a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.36.03-AM-768x626.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b08f519095f3c125a49a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.36.03-AM-1536x1251.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1706px) 100vw, 1706px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack: DEX<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Decentralized exchanges operate without a central authority or middlemen, allowing users to transact peer-to-peer with little risk of censorship<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>While DEXs historically suffer from price discrepancies across exchanges, the increasing popularity of DEX aggregating tools has tightened the spread across these exchanges<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"452\" height=\"170\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b10149103c685697162b_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.37.51-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3772\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Protocol for automated token swapping on Ethereum<\/li><li>ETH and ERC20 tokens are pooled in reserves, and the ratio of these assets determines the exchange rate<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"342\" height=\"150\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b13349103c348b971698_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.38.48-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3773\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Decentralized ERC20 exchange with token for staking<\/li><li>Similar to centralized alternatives, but trades are settled on-chain<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"326\" height=\"160\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b151bb83ab4b99fd7c77_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.39.20-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3774\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Protocol for peer-to-peer asset exchange on Ethereum<\/li><li>Native ZRX token used for governance and fees<\/li><li>Offers tools for other DEXs to implement<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1414\" height=\"832\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b17a4b9e5a5f43a182b2_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.39.59-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3775\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b17a4b9e5a5f43a182b2_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.39.59-AM.jpg 1414w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b17a4b9e5a5f43a182b2_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.39.59-AM-768x452.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1414px) 100vw, 1414px\" \/><figcaption>Volume by DEX<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>The DeFi Stack: Payments<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1358\" height=\"1134\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b1a7519095056925ab9c_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.40.46-AM-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3776\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b1a7519095056925ab9c_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.40.46-AM-1.jpg 1358w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b1a7519095056925ab9c_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.40.46-AM-1-768x641.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1358px) 100vw, 1358px\" \/><figcaption>Composability enables aggregators to stack DeFi building blocks, creating new payment applications<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Challenges Beyond DeFi: Cross-Fi<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3>What\u2019s holding #DeFi from mass adoption today?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Availability of fiat on \/ off ramps<\/li><li>Lack of financial privacy<\/li><li>Scalability \/ high gas costs<\/li><li>Smart contract \/ technical risk (and lack of insurance)<\/li><li>Lack of identity \/ credit scores leading to over-collateralization requirements<\/li><li>Friction around UX \/ UI<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Scalability \/ high gas costs<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2560\" height=\"877\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b24358e6cbbd3655c73a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.43.21-AM-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3777\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b24358e6cbbd3655c73a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.43.21-AM-scaled.jpg 2560w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b24358e6cbbd3655c73a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.43.21-AM-768x263.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b24358e6cbbd3655c73a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.43.21-AM-1536x526.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b24358e6cbbd3655c73a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.43.21-AM-2048x701.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" \/><figcaption>Multiple scalability solutions coming to market will enable more gas-intensive use cases<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Lack of identity \/ credit scores leading to over-collateralization requirements<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Differing approaches based on the applicant\u2019s credit profile:<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Unbanked or \u201cthin-file\u201d (no significant credit history or identity)<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Alternative credit scoring (<a href=\"https:\/\/tala.co\/about\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Tala, CELO<\/a>) &#8211; Rental, phone, TV payments, Bank account information (deposits\/withdrawals), Social media \/ mobile phone data, Public address credit history (<a href=\"https:\/\/graychain.net\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Graychain<\/a>)<\/li><li>P2P \/ social vouching (<a href=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/media\/building-the-future-of-cross-fi#\">VouchForMe<\/a>)<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<ol start=\"2\"><li>Existing credit, but no blockchain identity \/ credit score<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Integration of traditional credit scoring data (<a href=\"https:\/\/bloom.co\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Bloom<\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.colendi.com\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Colendi<\/a>)<\/li><li>Privacy preserving solutions (<a href=\"https:\/\/blog.enigma.co\/decentralizing-credit-with-enigma-440c6648b4d8\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Enigma<\/a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/www.springlabs.com\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Spring Labs<\/a>)<\/li><li>Decentralized identity solutions (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.uport.me\/\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">uPort<\/a>)<\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/blog.sendwyre.com\/community-driven-on-chain-compliance-d334e0f5962b\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Wyre\u2019s<\/a>&nbsp;ERC-721 compliance \/ identity token<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"590\" height=\"222\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b3835190952a4b25b3ab_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.48.40-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3778\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A proof-of-stake smart contract platform that allows people to send value to each other with only a phone number<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Reputation is attached to phone numbers and measured through the use of EigenTrust, a P2P reputation management algorithm based on mobile phone data and attestations<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Celo allows for multiple stable-value currencies where each coin is pegged to a measurable value such as the Dollar, Euro, the price of a barrel of oil, etc.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>cGLD, the native digital asset of Celo, is an ERC-20 compliant token and will be partially used to fund the reserve<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Smart contract \/ technical risk (and lack of insurance)<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>MakerDAO has established a security roadmap for the upcoming Multi-Collateral Dai launch, showcasing best practices:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1302\" height=\"788\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b3fd4b9e5a36eea190b8_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.50.29-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3779\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b3fd4b9e5a36eea190b8_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.50.29-AM.jpg 1302w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b3fd4b9e5a36eea190b8_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.50.29-AM-768x465.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1302px) 100vw, 1302px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Emergent solutions like NexusMutual provide \u201csmart contract cover\u201d to secure risk and potential bugs in code (i.e. DAO hack or Parity multi-sig freeze)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1498\" height=\"822\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b4244b9e5aee3ca191e5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.51.20-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3780\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b4244b9e5aee3ca191e5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.51.20-AM.jpg 1498w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b4244b9e5aee3ca191e5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.51.20-AM-768x421.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1498px) 100vw, 1498px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Availability of fiat on \/ off ramps<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Increasing competition should lead to fee compression<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Centralized<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"392\" height=\"136\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b59f4b9e5affc9a195cc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.57.37-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3781\"\/><figcaption>Fees n\/a<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"488\" height=\"136\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b5ba58e6cb487455e5c0_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.58.07-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3782\"\/><figcaption>$2.99 with bank or 3.99%with credit\/debit*<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"488\" height=\"192\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b5d331edea58c5b5655c_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.58.33-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3783\"\/><figcaption>0.75% transfer fee, or miner fee<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"484\" height=\"172\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b618bb83ab8cc8fda0e5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-9.59.42-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3784\"\/><figcaption>3% on purchase of up to $250<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h4>Non-custodial<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"400\" height=\"166\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b6544b9e5ae72ba19adc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.00.36-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3785\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Peer-to-peer trading platform to facilitate the sale\/purchase of crypto for fiat<\/li><li>Uses smart contracts to lock up crypto assets and wire transfers for payments<\/li><li>Only available with European banks, where Open Banking Laws allow oracles to verify transactions and notify smart contracts to unlock assets<\/li><li>Fees are up to 3% of the transaction<\/li><li>Currently only supporting ETH and DAI<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Friction around UX \/ UI<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><em>\u201cOver 90% of users who try to use a dApp will give up when told they need to download Metamask\u201d<\/em><\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Wallet SDKs enable a Web2 login experience with a username and password, removing the requirement to download a separate extension in order to use the app<\/li><li>Smart Contract Wallets can be programmed to have the same security guarantees as a traditional bank (account recovery, fraud protection, and withdrawal limits). Implemented via Smart Contract Wallets, Meta transactions allow users to use dApps immediately via sponsored gas fees, removing the need for users to pre-purchase crypto or install a browser extension<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1686\" height=\"314\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b70558e6cb25f355ec52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.29-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3786\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b70558e6cb25f355ec52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.29-AM.jpg 1686w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b70558e6cb25f355ec52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.29-AM-768x143.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b70558e6cb25f355ec52_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.29-AM-1536x286.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1686px) 100vw, 1686px\" \/><figcaption>Wallet SDKs<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1678\" height=\"714\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b71fbb83ab00cdfda6d5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.38-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3787\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b71fbb83ab00cdfda6d5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.38-AM.jpg 1678w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b71fbb83ab00cdfda6d5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.38-AM-768x327.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b71fbb83ab00cdfda6d5_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.03.38-AM-1536x654.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1678px) 100vw, 1678px\" \/><figcaption>Smart Contract Wallets<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Lack of Financial Privacy &amp; Auditability<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1298\" height=\"1182\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b75dbb83ab85bbfda81f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.05.06-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3788\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b75dbb83ab85bbfda81f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.05.06-AM.jpg 1298w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b75dbb83ab85bbfda81f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.05.06-AM-768x699.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1298px) 100vw, 1298px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"580\" height=\"230\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b79031edea9823b56e71_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.05.56-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3789\"\/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>proof of solvency, capacity-specific keys<\/li><li>supersonics, bulletproof, zether, authenticated data structures<\/li><li>privacy vs. regulatory compliance<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Harmony\u2019s contribution to DeFi &amp; Cross-Fi<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3184\" height=\"1368\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b7e851909540cc25d7bc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.07.20-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3790\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b7e851909540cc25d7bc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.07.20-AM.png 3184w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b7e851909540cc25d7bc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.07.20-AM-768x330.png 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b7e851909540cc25d7bc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.07.20-AM-1536x660.png 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b7e851909540cc25d7bc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.07.20-AM-2048x880.png 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 3184px) 100vw, 3184px\" \/><figcaption>Harmony\u2019s contribution to DeFi &amp; Cross-Fi<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Fiat Integrations &amp; dApp Payments via Carbon<\/li><li>Developer tools to port EVM compatible dApps<\/li><li>Bridges from ERC20 \/ BEP2 to native ONE token<\/li><li>Lower gas fees w\/o sacrificing decentralization<\/li><li>Unbiasable randomness<\/li><li>Decentralized exchange functionality<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Gateway: dApp Payment &amp; Fiat Integrations<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1360\" height=\"994\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b890519095e53c25de0b_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.10.16-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3791\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b890519095e53c25de0b_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.10.16-AM.jpg 1360w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b890519095e53c25de0b_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.10.16-AM-768x561.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1360px) 100vw, 1360px\" \/><figcaption>Carbon is helping issue a FDIC-insured stablecoin native on Harmony. dApps can enable any purchases in ONE tokens using Apple Pay and credit cards in a few lines of code.<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>30-second fiat on-ramp to ONE<\/li><li>Harmony-native stablecoins<\/li><li>5-line code to integrate<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2382\" height=\"1040\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b8e258e6cb088b55f8d3_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.11.32-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3792\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b8e258e6cb088b55f8d3_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.11.32-AM.jpg 2382w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b8e258e6cb088b55f8d3_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.11.32-AM-768x335.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b8e258e6cb088b55f8d3_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.11.32-AM-1536x671.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b8e258e6cb088b55f8d3_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.11.32-AM-2048x894.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2382px) 100vw, 2382px\" \/><figcaption>Scalability: Reduction in gas fees<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Decentralized market makers via Hummingbot<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"830\" height=\"226\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b910bb83ab20d8fdb5d9_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.12.24-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3793\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b910bb83ab20d8fdb5d9_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.12.24-AM.png 830w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b910bb83ab20d8fdb5d9_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.12.24-AM-768x209.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 830px) 100vw, 830px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Open finance, open source<\/li><li>102 decentralized market makers constituting 8% of ONE volume<\/li><li>for arbitrage, dex, algo trading<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1350\" height=\"1250\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b9474b9e5a3aeaa1b690_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.13.16-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3794\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b9474b9e5a3aeaa1b690_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.13.16-AM.jpg 1350w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9b9474b9e5a3aeaa1b690_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.13.16-AM-768x711.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1350px) 100vw, 1350px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Developer Tooling<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul><li><a href=\"https:\/\/github.com\/harmony-one\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Harmony Protocol<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/harmony.one\/api\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">API\u2019s<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/harmony.one\/sdk\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">SDK<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/harmony.one\/testnet\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Testnet<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/harmony.one\/h2o\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Smart Contracts<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Harmony cross-chain bridge<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1590\" height=\"898\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba3e58e6cb36f95601fc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.17.23-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3795\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba3e58e6cb36f95601fc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.17.23-AM.jpg 1590w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba3e58e6cb36f95601fc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.17.23-AM-768x434.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba3e58e6cb36f95601fc_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.17.23-AM-1536x868.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1590px) 100vw, 1590px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Gateway to swap $ONE BEP2 tokens to ERC20, and in the future, ERC20 to native mainnet $ONE tokens<\/li><li>Providing better liquidity for the $ONE ecosystem<\/li><li>Enabling cross-chain interoperability<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Randomness vs. Fairness<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1932\" height=\"1314\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba8e4b9e5a671ea1bd6a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.18.36-AM.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3796\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba8e4b9e5a671ea1bd6a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.18.36-AM.jpg 1932w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba8e4b9e5a671ea1bd6a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.18.36-AM-768x522.jpg 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9ba8e4b9e5a671ea1bd6a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.18.36-AM-1536x1045.jpg 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1932px) 100vw, 1932px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>States\/moves stored on chain<\/li><li>Unbiasable dice for random puzzles as fair tournaments<\/li><li>Built-in staking &amp; betting<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Current challenges within cross-border payments<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1578\" height=\"1162\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bad25190950e3725f17f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.19.52-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3797\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bad25190950e3725f17f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.19.52-AM.png 1578w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bad25190950e3725f17f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.19.52-AM-768x566.png 768w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bad25190950e3725f17f_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.19.52-AM-1536x1131.png 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1578px) 100vw, 1578px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1370\" height=\"182\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bae531edea703db57f2a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.20.10-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3798\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bae531edea703db57f2a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.20.10-AM.png 1370w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bae531edea703db57f2a_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.20.10-AM-768x102.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1370px) 100vw, 1370px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Remittance cost drivers:<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li>Inefficient correspondent banking systems<\/li><li>Lack of market competition in certain corridors<\/li><li>Regulation and compliance costs<\/li><li>Agent network infrastructure<\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>Estimated&nbsp;<strong>$32 billion<\/strong>&nbsp;in remittances aren\u2019t sent due to high transactional costs associated with cross-border money transfers<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cross-Fi: DeFi meets Cross-Border Payments<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Current challenges:<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Slow<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Multi-hop money movements between correspondent currency pairs can take between 1-5 days to fully settle<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Limited accessibility<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cash dependent transactions rely heavily on local distribution, which is scarce, especially in rural areas<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Limited trust<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Last mile transfers rely on fragmented P2P networks with centralized counterparties<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Friction across geographies \/ markets<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Current digital payment solutions can be limited in coverage (i.e. Grab cannot be used in China)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Harmony offering:<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Finality<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Harmony provides instant finality, reducing settlement time to seconds vs. days<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Digital wallets<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>1.7 billion adults remain unbanked, yet two-thirds of them own a mobile phone1<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Trust layer<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cryptography, combined with Harmony\u2019s immutable ledger, provides trust without the need for intermediaries or centralized 3rd parties<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Borderless<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Fully compliant regional solutions combined with low cost fiat on and off ramps reduce geographical frictions<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Harmony\u2019s Cross-Fi Solutions Roadmap<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<h4>Research<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Cross-Fi:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul><li>Transaction value proposition (settlement, peg, rates, identity)<\/li><li>Financial products with China \/ India \/ Vietnamese currency pairs<\/li><li>Remittance, billing, payroll in Europe<\/li><\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Privacy<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/medium.com\/harmony-one\/ring-signature-and-implementation-on-harmony-one-2d8465419cf9\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Ring Signature Implementation on Harmony<\/a>, enabling obfuscation of transactions behind a group of similar transactions<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Audible privacy financial transactions with Findora collaboration<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Tooling<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Cross-border payment stack (lending, identity, stablecoins)<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simplified on-boarding experience to enable mass adoption<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Development of fiat on \/ off ramps and exchange venues<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h4>Adoption<\/h4>\n\n\n\n<p>Decentralized credit facility platform, where users can use ONE as collateral to mint various fiat-pegged stablecoins<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Cross-border payment applications leveraging Harmony\u2019s scalability, fast finality, decentralization and low transaction costs<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u200d<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"3310\" height=\"260\" src=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bc99bb83abb6befdc910_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.27.25-AM.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-3799\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2020\/11\/5de9bc99bb83abb6befdc910_Screen-Shot-2019-12-06-at-10.27.25-AM.png 3310w, https:\/\/wavegp.com\/wp-content\/upload